    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.6.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, vim 8.2.4106\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux (Kernel 5.16.9-arch1-1)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.11.0-dev (60ef17e8)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nSystem package manager (pacman)\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\nnvim --clean\r\n:nowrap\r\nType any long line that exceeds the split or window width\r\nType another line below that is shorter than the window width\r\nNavigate to long line\r\n$ to go to the end of long line\r\nj to navigate down to short line\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nView to reset to column 0 to show the full short line as it fits within the window width. I specifically mean column 0 and **not** the first non-whitespace character.\r\n\r\nAs can be seen below with a bit of sample code Vim 8.2.4106 handles it in a way I would expect.\r\n![vim_01](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8584482/154588790-baee6150-13ea-4568-9eab-58d094dc076a.png)\r\nNavigating to the end of the long line using $:\r\n![vim_02](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8584482/154588844-20ca6f76-6f61-4aa1-881d-9960044aaab5.png)\r\nMoving down (only pressing j, no other inputs were made) to the line below:\r\n![vim_03](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8584482/154588868-4d07f01c-f5f2-4d4b-88be-a531a4f979e2.png)\r\n\r\n\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nThe cursor just pulls the view back to the first visible character but no further so the rest of the line can't be seen.\r\n\r\nSame code as above:\r\n![nvim_01](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8584482/154589287-81d00a2c-fdce-415b-bc9a-6fe4edd79ace.png)\r\nNavigating to the end of the long line with $:\r\n![nvim_02](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8584482/154589306-9e0af915-de87-4921-a864-529bd2373eef.png)\r\nMoving down (once again only pressing j):\r\n![nvim_03](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8584482/154589334-2105bc3e-d69c-4edc-b48c-84999cf22480.png)",
